TITLE: Creating Firebase Function to Listen for User Signups
DESCRIPTION: This function triggers on new user creation in Firebase Authentication. It retrieves the user's display name and email, then formats and sends a message to Slack using the webhook URL.
SOURCE: https://github.com/firebase/functions-samples/blob/main/Python/post-signup-event/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
exports.sendWelcomeMessageOnSlack = functions.auth.user().onCreate((user) => {
  const slackClient = new WebClient(slackWebhookUrl);

  const { displayName, email } = user;
  const text = `New user signed up:\nName: ${displayName || 'Not provided'}\nEmail: ${email}`;

  return slackClient.chat.postMessage({
    channel: '#general',
    text: text,
  });
});
```

