TITLE: Configuring Firebase Functions for Discord Alerts
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to set up a Firebase Cloud Function that sends alerts to a Discord channel. It imports necessary modules, initializes the Discord client, and defines a function to send messages to a specific channel.
SOURCE: https://github.com/firebase/functions-samples/blob/main/Python/alerts-to-discord/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const functions = require('firebase-functions');
const Discord = require('discord.js');

// Create a new webhook client
const webhookClient = new Discord.WebhookClient(
    functions.config().discord.webhook_id,
    functions.config().discord.webhook_token);

// This will allow us to send a message to a specific channel in Discord
const sendMessage = (message) => {
  webhookClient.send(message);
};
```

